  "prompt": "I have forgotten ssc cgl password, what should I do now?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your SSC CGL (Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level) password, follow these steps to recover or reset it:\n\n1. Visit the official SSC website (https://ssc.nic.in/)\n\n2. Go to the login section\n\n3. Look for the \"Forgot Password\" or \"Reset Password\" option\n\n4. You will typically need to:\n- Enter your registered username/registration number\n- Provide your registered mobile number or email\n- Verify your identity through OTP (One-Time Password)\n\n5. After verification, you can:\n- Create a new password\n- Reset your existing password\n\nAdditional tips:\n- Ensure you use the same email/mobile number used during registration\n- Keep your new password secure and memorable\n- If you face issues, contact SSC helpline or regional office\n- Have your registration details and documents ready\n\nImportant contact details:\n- SSC Helpdesk: 011-22520174\n- Website: https://ssc.nic.in/\n- Email: help.ssc@nic.in\n\nIf online methods don't work, you may need to contact SSC directly for personalized assistance.",
